  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nWhen the `PeerPool` has no peers we get a division by zero error.\r\n\r\n```\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/chain.py\", line 133, in sync\r\n    await self._sync(peer)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/chain.py\", line 172, in _sync\r\n    head_number = await self._process_headers(peer, headers)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/chain.py\", line 194, in _process_headers\r\n    'receipt')\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/chain.py\", line 229, in _download_block_parts\r\n    pending_replies = request_func(missing)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/chain.py\", line 292, in request_receipts\r\n    return self._request_block_parts(headers, self._send_get_receipts)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/chain.py\", line 260, in _request_block_parts\r\n    length = math.ceil(len(headers) / len(self.peer_pool.peers))\r\nZeroDivisionError: division by zero\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nTODO: how do we fix this\r\n",
