    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is a race condition, I'm afraid. The chain syncer runs `sync()` in the background when it hears about a new peer/block, and it looks like by the time `sync()` got scheduled the `PeerPool` had lost all its peers. I guess we need to check for that at the beginning of `sync()` and abort if it's the case",
